body:
I was able to reproduce same issue with vanilla example from the [documentation](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/rpc/ns-debug#javascript-based-tracing) `tracer`
```javascript
ethereum:~# cat /tmp/tracer
{data: [], fault: function(log) {}, step: function(log) {
    if (log.op.toString() == "CALL") this.data.push(log.stack.peek(0));
}, result: function() {
    return this.data;
}
}
```
or
```javascript
ethereum:~# cat /tmp/tracer
{data: [], fault: function(log) {}, step: function(log) {}, result: function() {
    return this.data;
}
}
```
```bash
ethereum:~# curl 127.0.0.1:8545 -H "Content-Type: application/json" --max-time 3 -s -d '{"id":"1","jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"debug_traceBlockByNumber","params":["0xe33563",{"tracer":"`cat /tmp/tracer`"}]}'
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":"1","error":{"code":-32000,"message":"method handler crashed"}}
```

Logs look like this
```
Jun  6 10:52:20 erigon-node erigon[6652]: [EROR] [06-06|10:52:20.338] RPC method debug_traceBlockByNumber crashed: AssertFunction
Jun  6 10:52:20 erigon-node erigon[6652]: [service.go:217 panic.go:838 jsvm.go:198 tracer.go:552 tracer.go:636 interpreter.go:313 evm.go:75 evm.go:273 state_transition.go:412 state_transition.go:230 tracing.go:143 tracing.go:93 tracing.go:25 value.go:556 value.go:339 service.go:222 handler.go:458 handler.go:398 handler.go:347 handler.go:185 handler.go:275 asm_amd64.s:1571]
Jun  6 10:52:20 erigon-node erigon[6652]: [WARN] [06-06|10:52:20.338] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:42458 method=debug_traceBlockByNumber reqid=1 t=7.378676ms err="method handler crashed"

```

This one also crashes with `method handler crashed`:
```
{
  "method": "debug_traceBlockByNumber",
  "params": [
    "0xC65D45",
    {
      "tracer": "prestateTracer"
    }
  ],
